clinical_study.brief_title: Phase 1 Study To Test the Bioequivalence Between Two 25 mg Tablets vs. One 50 mg Tablet Under Fast/Fed Condition and Evaluate Food Effect of Desvenlafaxine Succinate Sustained Release (DVS SR)
clinical_study.official_title: Phase 1, Open-Label, Randomized, Single-Dose, 4-Treatment, 4-Period Crossover Bioequivalence Study Comparing 25 Mg and 50 Mg Formulations of DVS-233 SR and Investigate Food Effect on 50 Mg Formulations of DVS-233 SR Tablet Under Fed and Fasted Conditions

brief_summary.textblock:
To determine the bioequivalence of 2 tablets of 25 mg sustained release (SR) formulation of DVS and 1 tablet of 50 mg SR formulation of DVS under fed and fast conditions.
To investigate the effect of high-fat meal on pharmacokinetics of desvenlafaxine after administration of 50 mg SR formulation of DVS.

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
- Healthy male and female subjects.
Exclusion Criteria:
- Evidence or history of clinically significant hematological, renal, endocrine, pulmonary, gastrointestinal, cardiovascular, hepatic, psychiatric, neurologic, or allergic disease

participant_flow.pre_assignment_details: Participants randomized to an open-label treatment sequence beginning in Period 1 with 25 milligrams as 2 tablets (25 mg*2) in fed state=A; or a 50 mg tablet in fed state=B; or 25 mg*2 tablets in fasted state=C; or a 50 mg tablet in fasted state=D in a cross-over, 4-period design. Treatment groups sequenced as: ABCD, BADC, CDAB, and DCBA.

group.title: DVS SR 25 mg*2 Fed (A) First
group.description: Desvenlafaxine sustained release (DVS SR) formulation (PF-0212375) 25 milligrams (mg) as 2 tablets (25 mg*2) on Day 1 of study period in fed state (finished a high-fat breakfast 20 minutes prior to dosing).

group.title: DVS SR 50 mg Fed (B) First
group.description: DVS SR 50 mg tablet on Day 1 of study period in fed state.

group.title: DVS SR 25 mg*2 Fasted (C) First
group.description: DVS SR 25 mg*2 tablets on Day 1 of study period in fasted state (fasted 8 hours prior to dosing).

group.title: DVS SR 50 mg Fasted (D) First
group.description: DVS SR 50 mg tablet on Day 1 of study period in fasted state.

participants_list.participants: Discontinued participant received treatment A of sequence ABCD.

measure.description: Area under the plasma concentration versus time curve from time zero (pre-dose) to 48 hours post dose; measured as nanograms multiplied by hours divided by milliliters (ng*hr/mL).

analysis.groups_desc: DVS SR 25 mg*2 fasted (test); DVS SR 50 mg fasted (reference). Natural log transformed AUC48: mixed models analysis with sequence, period, treatment (formulation by food status) as fixed effects and subject within sequence as a random effect.
analysis.non_inferiority_desc: Bioequivalence of the two treatments was to be concluded if the 90% CIs for the ratio of adjusted geometric means for AUC48 fell wholly within (80%, 125%).
analysis.estimate_desc: Adjusted mean difference and the 90% CI for the difference were exponentiated to provide an estimate of the ratio of adjusted geometric means (test/reference).

analysis.groups_desc: DVS SR 25 mg*2 fed (test); DVS SR 50 mg fed (reference). Natural log transformed AUC48: mixed models analysis with sequence, period, treatment (formulation by food status) as fixed effects and subject within sequence as a random effect.

reported_events.desc: Same event may appear as both an AE and SAE, however, are presented as distinct events; may be categorized as SAE in 1 subject and as non-SAE in another, or 1 subject may have experienced both an SAE and non-SAE during study. Participants are counted multiple times due to the transition through the cross-over sequences.
